# Useful bits of info from Piazza posts.

### Using CuPy defined functions
We are allowed to use things like cp.dot and cp.linalg.norm to implement the dot product and cosine distance functions. 
Apparently the first task is "simple and designed just for you to warm up".

### Installing NVCC
We are meant to add NVCC to our environment. 
https://anaconda.org/nvidia/cuda-nvcc
Choose the version that matches the CUDA version displayed in the top-right corner of the output when you run nvidia-smi.
